The paper discusses the evaluation of creativity in co-creative systems, which involves collaboration between computer programs and human users. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational creativity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the unique qualities of co-creative systems, which may involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper provides examples of co-creative systems in various domains, including art, humor, games, and robotics, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
